title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.2: INTEGRATED HIGH-IMPACT HEALTH AND NUTRITION SERVICES.

description.narrative: Health systems and communities in targeted localities have strengthened capacities and deliver integrated high-impact health and nutrition services, which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, more children under the age of 5 years and women of reproductive age utilize high-impact, quality health and nutrition services.

title.narrative: Health systems and communities in targeted localities have strengthened capacities and deliver integrated high-impact health and nutrition services

description.narrative: Facility and community platforms, strengthened by implementing partners, were able to deliver integrated models for health services to nearly 23.8 million boys, girls, women and men, including those affected by humanitarian crises, across Sudan. Over half a million boys and girls among IDPs and refugees were immunized against measles, while additional 762,750 accessed integrated management of childhood illness (IMCI) services and 6.1 million were reached with vitaminA supplementation. Over 1,030 community health workers gained knowledge and skills to deliver high-impact interventions. The MOH was able to maintain supplies of oral rehydration salts (ORS) throughout the year without any stock-outs. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
